al boundaries and resonates powerfully with contemporary readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aHousewivesxFictionxItaly. 0aHousewiveszItalyvFiction. 0aItalian literature. 4aArea Studies : Italian Studies. 4aLiterature : Comparative Literature. 4aLiterature : Literature. 4aLiterature : Translation. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aFeltrin-Morris, Marella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143842813040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438428130423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438428130/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles